At ALS, we encourage you to dream big.

When you join us, you’ll be part of a global team harnessing the power of scientific testing and data-driven insights to build a healthier future.

General Accountability:

The Laboratory Assistant will work as part of the Spectroscopy team to accomplish a variety of lab tasks and lab maintenance. These responsibilities will include conducting solution preparation, instrument batching, and some routine instrument analyses of geological samples in accordance with ALS Health and Safety policies and ALS quality procedures.

Specific Responsibilities


Prepare instrument solutions and perform sample dilutions;
Prepare instrument run batches for analysis;
Assist in instrument calibration setup and operations;
Maintain the timely storage and disposal of sample solutions for the department;
Prioritize workloads according to daily stats and turnaround commitments;
Maintain and organize instrument logs, equipment, reagent, and solution records;
Operate and perform routine analyses and maintenance on ICP-AES, ICP-MS, and AAS instruments;
Evaluate data using instrument software and GEMS;
Identify & correct QC-related issues by ensuring the quality of the analytical data meets ALS standards;
Maintain a clean and safe work environment and communicate all safety concerns to Operations Supervisor or Manager;
Assist in other sections of the laboratory as required;
Additional duties as assigned by Senior Laboratory Analyst, Operations Supervisor, or Manager.


Required Knowledge, Skills & Abilities:


Highly organized and detail-oriented with proven ability to work to deadlines;
Ability to work independently or as a part of a team in a fast-paced environment;
Good organizational, analytical, and mechanical skills;
Capable of managing workflow in a time-efficient and quality-conscious manner;
Good English communication skills both written and verbal;
Good MS Office skills, specifically MS Word, Excel, and Outlook;
Full training will be provided.


Required Qualifications:


High school completion or equivalent required;
Some post-secondary chemistry courses are preferred;
Minimum of 1-year laboratory experience in analytical chemistry or related field preferred.


Physical Demands:


Ability to lift up to 45lbs;
Ability to sit and/or stand for up to 7.5 hours per day;
Ability to work in afternoon and night shifts.
Manual dexterity to perform repetitive tasks.
Please note that ALS Group operates 24/7 and will require day, afternoon, and graveyard shift work including weekends.


Our benefits include:


An estimated hourly pay of $22.77 at the time of posting. Individual compensation is determined by factors such as job-related skills, relevant experience, education and/or training.
Additional shift premiums of $2 per hour for evening shifts and $4 per hour for night shifts, if applicable.
Structured wage increases.
Comprehensive benefit package specific to your work status (including extended medical, dental, and vision coverage, access to company perks, life and disability insurance, retirement plan with company match, employee assistance and wellness programs).
Additional vacation days for years of service.
Business support for education or training after 9 months with the company.
Learning & development opportunities (unlimited access to e-learnings and more).


Please note: Benefits vary based on employee status.

Working at ALS

The ALS team is a diverse and dedicated community united by our passion to make a difference in the world.

Our values are important to us, and shape how we work, how we treat each other and how we recognise excellence.

At ALS, you’ll be supported to develop new skills and reach your full potential. We invest in our people with programs and opportunities that help you build a diverse career with us.

We want everyone to have a safe, flexible and rewarding career that makes a positive impact on our people, the planet and our communities.

Everyone Matters

ALS is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and is committed to fostering an inclusive work environment where the strengths and perspectives of each employee are both recognised and valued.

Qualified candidates will be considered without regard to race, colour, religion, national origin, military or veteran status, gender, age, disabilities, sexual orientation, gender identity, pregnancy and pregnancy-related conditions, genetic information and any other characteristics protected by the law. We invite resumes from all interested parties, including women, First Nations, Metis and Inuit persons, members of minority groups, and persons living with disabilities.  

ALS also welcomes applications from people with all levels of ability. Reasonable adjustments to support candidates throughout the recruitment process are available upon request. 

Eligibility

To be eligible to work at ALS you must be a Citizen or Permanent Resident of the country you are applying for, or either hold or be able to obtain, a valid working visa.

How To Apply

Please apply on-line and provide a resume & cover letter that best demonstrate your motivation and ability to meet the requirements of this role.
